ðŸ† Main Challenge: Check for Duplicates

let numbers = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 1];

// Use a Set to check uniqueness
let hasDuplicate = new Set(numbers).size !== numbers.length;

if (hasDuplicate) {
  console.log("Duplicates found");
} else {
  console.log("No duplicates");
}
// Output: "Duplicates found"

ðŸ‘‰ Kid-style explanation:
Think of giving every student in class a roll number ðŸŽ’.

If two kids get the same roll number âž ðŸš¨ duplicate!

If everyone has a unique roll number âž âœ… no duplicates.



