âš¡ Pro Tip: You can also count duplicates:

let arr = [1, 2, 2, 3, 4, 4, 4];
let count = {};

arr.forEach(num => count[num] = (count[num] || 0) + 1);

console.log(count); // { '1': 1, '2': 2, '3': 1, '4': 3 }

ðŸ‘‰ This not only detects duplicates but also tells you how many times they occur!



